# CVE-2026-27601 - underscore.js DoS via flatten with recursive structures.
#
# The flagged 1.13.7 copy is a vendored static JS asset inside
# nbclassic/static/components/underscore/package.json, not the
# server-side underscore Python package (we don't depend on either).
# It comes from the quay.io/jupyter/base-notebook base image; no
# released nbclassic refreshes the bundled underscore yet, and we
# don't expose nbclassic's classic UI in these notebooks.
#
# Re-evaluate when the upstream base image bumps nbclassic / drops
# the vendored underscore.
CVE-2026-27601

# CVE-2025-2000 - qiskit QPY arbitrary code execution (CRITICAL).
# CVE-2025-1403 - qiskit QPY denial of service (HIGH).
#
# These affect Qiskit < 1.4.2 (RCE) and < 1.3.0 (DoS) respectively.
# We deliberately publish the 1.0/1.1/1.2/1.3 images for historical
# reproducibility of notebooks/tutorials/papers from those eras; there
# is no 1.0/1.1/1.2 release with the fixes, and bumping qiskit would
# defeat the purpose. The CVEs require a user to load a malicious
# .qpy file (no network exposure), and the README warns users pulling
# 1.x tags about the inherited risk.
#
# Trivy reports these as "fixed" against newer versions, so the
# entries here only suppress findings for the old qiskit minors we
# ship by design; a future qiskit 2.x or current-stream regression
# would not silently slip through unless it shared the same CVE id.
CVE-2025-2000
CVE-2025-1403

